

	 
         this is the only show that i watch on a daily basis now that oprah is doing reruns. it's been my favorite cartoon for the past four years, and in my opinion, far surpasses all the other cartoons for kids these days in terms of entertainment and educational value. i might not have learned much from the classrooms in elementary school, but this show reminds me of all the valuable lessons that i picked up on the playground, stuff about friendship and acceptance and survival that we might have forgotten as we grew up. the characters crack me up too (mikey's my favorite). i hope it's still around by the time i have a kid.
     
    
